.TH "in6_pton" 9 "in6_pton" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
in6_pton \- convert an IPv6 address from literal to binary representation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" in6_pton
.BI "(const char *src "  ","
.BI "int srclen "  ","
.BI "u8 *dst "  ","
.BI "int delim "  ","
.BI "const char **end "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "src" 12
the start of the IPv6 address string
.IP "srclen" 12
the length of the string, -1 means strlen(src)
.IP "dst" 12
the binary (u8[16] array) representation of the IPv6 address
.IP "delim" 12
the delimiter of the IPv6 address in \fIsrc\fP, -1 means no delimiter
.IP "end" 12
A pointer to the end of the parsed string will be placed here
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return one on success, return zero when any error occurs
and \fIend\fP will point to the end of the parsed string.
